920.question: When they say "comparable performance", how much of a performance drop do these new embeddings result in?
920.response: {'Answer': 'The new embeddings show a slight performance drop in link prediction metrics with a decrease in MRR from 31.6 to 30.4 and a decrease in hits@10 from 48.3% to 46.8%, while MR has improved from 121.9 to 111.9. However, for triple classification, the proposed method shows an improvement with AUC increasing from 72.9% to 73.2% and accuracy from 63.2% to 67.6%.'}
920.answer: Performance was comparable, with the proposed method quite close and sometimes exceeding performance of baseline method.
